HEADWORD: clitellus
<hw>cli*tel"lus</hw> <pr>(kl⟦icr⟧*t⟦ecr⟧l"l⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., prob. fr. L. <ets>clitellae</ets> a
packsadle.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A thickened glandular portion
of the body of the adult earthworm, consisting of several united
segments modified for reproductive purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

